description.narrative: Child protection services were strengthened to also respond to the COVID-19 emergency, with more than 14,000 children at risk of or experiencing harm and unnecessary family separation benefiting from direct services. UNICEF actively engaged in ‘preparedness and response' activities in the context of COVID-19, focusing on protecting children in alternative care, adapting case management practices and deploying additional social workers in all 25 provinces. A key step forward was the launch of Primero, a digital case management tool, interoperable with NGOs, improving collaboration and referrals as well as representing a backbone of a nationwide child protection practice | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/08/2020
